This project implements a smart environment monitoring system using an STM32-based trainer kit. It uses sensors to measure temperature, humidity, and light intensity in real-time. The STM32 processes the sensor data and categorizes environmental conditions. This system helps in enabling smart automation in homes and industries.

🎯 Objectives
To measure temperature and humidity using DHT11 sensor
To detect ambient light intensity using an LDR
To display the results on an OLED display for real-time visualization 
To develop a basic real-time environmental monitoring system
